    <text id="R12745635T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Union General Darius Couch reports from Chambersburg to General Smith on the
                    situation in Pennsylvania in July, 1863. He mentions ordering shoes to be sent
                    to Chambersburg for distribution to general Smith's command.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Brig.-Gen. Smith:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-07-10">July 10, 1863</date><time>--9 p. m.</time>
                        <name type="place">Chambersburg,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>Note received, &amp;c. I cannot give you an order to join Meade, not knowing
                    about your position in reference to the Army of the Potomac. With my present
                    force, if you go forward, I must remain here for a time. If it is in accordance
                    with Meade's wishes, go by all means. Capt. Potter will see you to-night and
                    explain matters.</p>
                <p>There is no difficulty in getting provisions now. I have set that all right.
                    Provisions have been sent to Gettysburg for you. Let me know if you leave.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Respectfully, yours,</salute>
                    <signed>D. N. COUCH,<lb/> Maj.-Gen.</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">P. S.--I ordered 1,000 pairs of shoes from Shippensburg
                        for you, to be brought here to-day.</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
